<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-12T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="6" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d6">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">710 Conference W And PW/1–1245:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-12T17:00:00-05:00">January 12, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 7:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>42. When conveying message contained in Department’s circular
                                telegram January 11, 7 p.m., this morning Foreign Office informed
                                that agenda mentioned in Mexican invitation to conference received
                                here corresponded exactly with that in Department’s circular January
                                5, 3 p.m.</p>
                            <pb facs="0020" n="6" xml:id="pg_6"/>
                            <p>Secretary General<note n="6" xml:id="d6fn6">Javier Correa, Secretary
                                    General of the Peruvian Foreign Office.</note> has now
                                telephoned that his Government approves this agenda without
                                additional suggestions.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>